_**This post is part of our special coverage of[Bahrain Protests
2011](https://globalvoicesonline.org/specialcoverage/bahrain-
protests-2011/).**_

After a [morning raid](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2011/02/17/bahrain-
breaking-news-police-attack-protesters-at-pearl-roundabout/) this Thursday 17
February, 2011, on protesters at Lulu Roundabout in Bahraini capital Manama,
reports have surfaced of army tanks heading towards the city.

> @[ahmed289](http://www.twitter.com/ahmed289)
> @[yslaise](http://www.twitter.com/yslaise) http://plixi.com/p/77971560

[![Army vehicles in Riffa heading towards the Bahraini capital Manama. Image
by @ahmed289.](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2011/02/tanksinriffa-375x277.jpg)](http://plixi.com/p/77971560)

Army vehicles in Riffa heading towards the Bahraini capital Manama. Image by
@ahmed289.

This [video](http://www.twitvid.com/IMZKO) by TwitVid user Ali Al Saeed shows
tanks driving towards Manama from the nearby city of Riffa.

> @[alialsaee](http://www.twitter.com/alialsaeed)d <http://twitvid.com/IMZKO>
> – Armored army vehicles driving towards Manama from Riffa.

